#achievement(title: [Immunomodulatory Therapeutic Approaches])[
Low-dose naltrexone (LDN), originally investigated for immune modulation, shows 73.9% positive response rates in ME/CFS @Cabanas2021 through restoration of TRPM3 ion channel function in natural killer cells. This mechanism-based approach exemplifies how immunologic expertise translates to novel ME/CFS therapeutics.
]
